<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="143" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,669,1042]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,268,810,834]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" reason="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brauns" authorityYear="1889" box="[274,440,811,834]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Stauropoctonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[274,440,811,834]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Stauropoctonus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is moderately to very large sized wasps and can be distinguished from other ophionine genera by combination of following characters: (1) Mandible more or less strongly taped and twisted; (2) Ocelli very large (i.e. posterior ocellus touching or close to eye); (3) Occipital carina virtually always absent; (4) Mesopleural furrow strong; (5) Discosubmaginal cell of fore wing without sclerites; (6) Fore tibial spur without a trace of membranous flange behind macrotrichial comb, and (7) distal margin of mid and hind trochantelli produced into a long curved acute tooth. Among these characters, (3) and (7) are rather rare within the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shuckard" authorityYear="1840" box="[735,863,983,1007]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophioninae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Ophioninae</taxonomicName>
. See 
<bibRefCitation author="Shimizu, S. &amp; Lima, A. R." box="[919,1179,983,1008]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" pagination="34 - 47" refId="ref4578" refString="Shimizu, S. &amp; Lima, A. R. (2017) Taxonomic revision of the genus Stauropoctonus Brauns, 1889 (Hymenoptera: Ichneumonidae: Ophioninae) in Japan. Entomological Science, 21 (1), 34 - 47. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / ens. 12279" type="journal article" year="2017">Shimizu &amp; Lima (2017)</bibRefCitation>
for detailed description and diagnosis.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
